<br>
Factual parse info from my logs:<br>
<br>
SCF3 pre-PoP at level 60<br>
- 9893 casts of SoFB, crit percentage 7.34 <br>
- 3880 casts of SoS, crit percentage 7.23<br>
<br>
SCF3 w/ PoP at level 60 - 61<br>
- 672 casts of SoFB, crit percentage 7.31<br>
- 340 casts of FBoT, crit percentage 6.98<br>
<br>
SCF3 + FuryOfMagic1 w/ PoP at level 61 - 63<br>
- 880 casts of SoFB, crit percentage 7.02<br>
- 568 casts of FBoT, crit percentage 6.88<br>
- 773 casts of BlackSteel, crit percentage 7.11<br>
<br>
If you look here SCF3 Pre Pop has over 10000 nukes parsed. Then for pop only 1000 nukes parsed without fury of magic. Finally we have fury of magic 1 with only 2000 ~ nukes. THIS IS NOT ENOUGH TO GET ANY FACTS FROM FURY OF MAGIC AA SKILL. <br>
<br>
Right now I have fury of magic 3, this skill raises up in point cost at 3 6 9 totaling up to 18 points spent.Fury of magic mastery the wizard aa skill (they do not get fury of magic) costs 2 4 6 for a total of 12 points spent. <br>
My estimate is that level 1 fury of magic will give LITTLE TO NO EFFECT on your crit rate and the real raises will be at level 2 and 3. The skill at level 3 should raise crits by 3.5 % from 7 % MAX. I draw this from the fact that wizards aa skill when parsed show a 3.5 % crit increase at level 3 and level 1 fury of magic mastery only giving around .5 % increase in crit rate.<br>
<br>
I suspect the reason why wizards have fury of magic mastery and mages have fury of magic is because way back during luclin whoever was balancing classes screwed up and didn't give some classes aa skills at higher cost and others at lower cost like a paladin should pay more than a mage for spell casting fury but less than a mage for natural durability. This would cause a situation where later dev cannot alter peoples aa windows without basiclly refunding everything and then redoing all the aa stuff giving people a chance to redo everything because the code would probably be far too much effort to change at that point. So instead they gave wizards a totally different aa skill had the same effect but allowed them to make their class pay less points for the same effect cause after all they are supposed to be the best nuker.<br>
<br>
Basicly I wouldn't take those parses for fury of magic and post pop until ALOT more nukes are parsed THOUSANDS more not hundreds. Yes fury of magic 3 isn't the greatest skill of all time, if you feel the need to moan that it isn't the greatest effect and costs too many points for not alot of gain. Then by all means start another thread when we find out the real crit percentage of fury of magic 3, thats not my gripe but don't send bug reports, whine etc untill you have more accurate information than so few nukes parsed. <br>
<br>
Gonain <br>
Xegony <br>
